title: USNDC Database Schema
description: United States National Data Center seismic monitoring database schema

ACTIVE_ID.description: The active_id table is used to track events or arrivals bein g actively worked interactively to prevent the same event/ar rival from being worked by more than one individual.

AFFILIATION.description: The affiliation table groups stations into networks.

TIME.comment: Starting time for station in network

ALGORITHM.description: The algorithm table describes the algorithm and valid time p eriod

ON_DATE.comment: The date the algorithm first became active or was created

OFF_DATE.comment: The date the algorithm was removed from the system or made obsolete

ALPHASITE.description: The alphasite table is used for tracking continuous data con nections by the DLMan application. For a given station, ther e must be a row in the table for each address from which the station may send continuous data. The columns prefdlid and prefport describe the preferred DLMan connection for the sta tion. DLMan fills in dlid and time while a station is active ly connected. The column dlid indicates to which dlid the st ation is currently connected (may be different from prefdlid ) and the column time is the system time for the last activi ty on the station's connection (not the time of any data rec eived). For stations that are not connected, time and dlid a re zero.

CON_ALLOWED.comment: Status on whether DLMAN is allowed to connect to this channel or not

TIME.comment: Clock time of most recent activity

AMP3C.description: The amp3c table contains amplitude measurements made on thre e-component data for a specific detection.

CFREQ.comment: Center frequency of filter band amplitude is measured on

AMPDESCRIPT.description: The ampdescript table contains descriptions of how amplitude measurements in amplitude were made.

TOFF.comment: Offset from theoretical or observed arrival time

GVLO.comment: Low group velocity for measurement window (km/sec)

GVHI.comment: High group velocity for measurement window kilometers per second (km/sec)

AMPLITUDE.description: The amplitude table contains arrival-based and origin-based amplitude measurements. The amplitude measurement is describ ed in ampdescript.

INARRIVAL.comment: y or n flag indicating if amplitude (amp) is the same as the amp in the arrival table

AMPLITUDE_DYN_PARS_DBL.description: The amplitude_dyn_pars_dbl table will store amplitude parame ters and metadata (float values). Each record will contain o nly one piece of information.

GROUP_NAME.comment: General function or purpose where attribute is used (e.g. FK)

AMPLITUDE_DYN_PARS_INT.description: The amplitude_dyn_pars_int table will store amplitude parame ters and metadata (integer values). Each record will contain only one piece of information.

GROUP_NAME.comment: General function or purpose where attribute is used (e.g. FK)

AMPLITUDE_DYN_PARS_STR.description: The amplitude_dyn_pars_str table will store amplitude parame ters and metadata (string values). Each record will contain only one piece of information.

GROUP_NAME.comment: General function or purpose where attribute is used (e.g. FK)

AOI.description: The aoi table contains geographic characteristics of a parti cluar region of the Earth, based on five criteria: aoi_geoch ar, depth_geochar, lfaoi_geochar, seismic_geochar, and terra in_geochar. The entire content of this table is classified S ECRET.

AOI_GEOCHAR.comment: Area of interest geographic region characteristic

LFAOI_GEOCHAR.comment: Look Forward Area of interest geographic region characteristic

APMA.description: The apma table contains results of particle motion analysis for a specific detection.

ARRIVAL.description: The arrival table contains summary information about arrival s.

ARRIVAL_DYN_PARS_DBL.description: The arrival_dyn_pars_dbl table will store arrival parameters and metadata (float values). Each record will contain only one piece of information.

GROUP_NAME.comment: General function or purpose where attribute is used (e.g. DETECT, ONSET, FK)

ARRIVAL_DYN_PARS_INT.description: The arrival_dyn_pars_int table will store arrival parameters and metadata (integer values). Each record will contain onl y one piece of information.

GROUP_NAME.comment: General function or purpose where attribute is used (e.g. DETECT, ONSET, FK)

ARRIVAL_DYN_PARS_STR.description: The arrival_dyn_pars_str table will store arrival parameters and metadata (string values). Each record will contain only one piece of information.

GROUP_NAME.comment: General function or purpose where attribute is used (e.g. DETECT, ONSET, FK)

ARRIVAL_TAG.description: The arrival_tag table contains information to indicate which mode was used to generate the arrival.

PROCESS_MODE.comment: Processing mode used to generate arrival

AR_INFO.description: The ar_info table contains information about arrival observa tions used in event location. This includes the predicted ob servation values, the model used to predict the values, and all uncertainties associated with that observation.

VMODEL.comment: Velocity model for theoretical travel time (TT) and slowness (SLO)

TOTAL_TRAVEL_TIME.comment: Predicted travel time including all corrections (seconds)

ELLIP_CORR.comment: Time correction due to earth's ellipticity (seconds)

ELEV_CORR.comment: Time correction due to station elevation (seconds)

BULK_STATIC_STA_CORR.comment: Static station correction to travel time (seconds)

TT_MODEL_PLUS_MEAS_ERROR.comment: Combined travel time model and measurement uncertainty (seconds)

AZ_MODEL_PLUS_MEAS_ERROR.comment: Combined azimuth model and measurement uncertainty (degrees)

SL_MODEL_PLUS_MEAS_ERROR.comment: Combined slowness model and measurement uncertainty (s/deg)

TIME_IMPORT.comment: Weight applied to travel time in event solution

AZ_IMPORT.comment: Weight applied to azimuth in event solution

SLOW_IMPORT.comment: Weight applied to slowness in event solution

SLOW_VEC_RES.comment: Residual between predicted and observed FK vector (s/deg)

ASSOC.description: The assoc table contains information that connects arrivals (entries in the arrival table) to a particular origin.

ASSOC_GA.description: The assoc_ga table is used by the GA application to store te mporary associations.

ASSOC_GA_DEL.description: The assoc_ga_del table is used by the GA application to stor e deleted associations for later reference, if necessary.

BEAM.description: The beam table stores the azimuth and slowness used during t he production of a beam. Whenever an origin beam is produced , a beam record is also produced and linked through the wfid to the beam waveform stored in the wfdisc table.

FILTERID.comment: This is a TBD field created in anticipation of the Persistent Parameter module

AOI_GEOCHAR.comment: Area of interest geographic region characteristic

BULLETIN_RELEASE_EXPORT.description: The bulletin release export table contains information to tr ack Event Release files in the event they are not recieved a t the intended destination.

ERP_SEQ.comment: Event Release Process export sequence number

BUTTERWORTH_FILTER.description: The butterworth_filter table stores filter processing parame ter.

FILTERID.comment: ID number of a filter processing parameter

FILTER_TYPE.comment: Type of Butterworth filter (BP, LP, HP)

FILTER_ZEROPH.comment: This is a flag to indicate zero-phase filtering. If this is set to 0, the filter is not zero-phase. If this is set to 1, the filter is zero-phase i.e. no phase lag or group delay.

CHANNAME.description: The channame table provides mapping between channel and stat ion names.

CHAN_GROUPS.description: The chan_groups table is used to indicate which sta/chan pai rs belong to a given class/name (wfactivity) group.

DURATION.comment: Duration in seconds of the time region

INWFACTIVITY.comment: Indicates whether class/name/duration is in wfactivity or not

CLASSIFICATION.description: Contains the table ID information for other tables. Makes u p the overall classification consisting of classification le vel, control markings office of primary responsibility, sour ce used for classification and declassification instructions .

CLASS_OPR_ID.comment: ID for the classification_opr table. This is the agency, office (or OPR) responsible for classification and classification date.

ON_DATE.comment: The date the classification becomes active.

OFF_DATE.comment: The date the classification becomes inactive or obsolete.

CLASSIFICATION_LEVEL.description: Provides the overall classification for marking the top and bottom of documents.

PARAGRAPH_MARK.comment: Abbreviated classification for paragraph marking i.e. UNCLASSIFIED = U.

CLASSIFICATION_LOOKUP.description: Looks up the classification information in the classificatio n table.

APPLICATION.comment: The name of the application using the security marking, e.g. ARS, McTool.

ON_DATE.comment: The date the classification becomes active.

OFF_DATE.comment: The date the classification becomes inactive or obsolete.

CLASSIFICATION_OPR.description: Used to contain the agency, office (or OPR) responsible for classification

CLASSIFICATION_REFER_TO.description: The classification_refer_to table will contain the "Refer to :..." information for the Exective Order Box.

CLASS_REFER.comment: The classification_refer_to.class_refer contains the "Refer to" string which follows the the "Declassify On" part of the Exective Order Box. It provides the source to refer to in order to properly de classify something.

CLASS_DECLASS_ID.description: Contains the declassification date and reference information . Used as part of the Executive Order Box.

CLASS_DERIVED_ID.description: Identification of the source of classification (Classified b y or Derived From line). Part of the Executive Order Box.

CLASS_DERIVED.comment: The source of the classification, i.e. classified by or derived from.

CLASS_DISSEM_ID.description: Contains the control markings of the overall security markin g. i.e. FOUO, NOFORN

CLASS_DISSEM.comment: The abbreviated control marking which may follow the classification.

PARAGRAPH_MARK.comment: The paragraph control marking. May be an abbreviated version of the class_dissem control marking.

CLUSTER_INFO.description: The cluster_info table contains information relating to the cluster of events. It relates to versions of the same cluste r (same events) together. It also contains the orid of the e vent closest to the center of the cluster and the radius of the cluster.

PREFOR.comment: Origin that is closest to the center of the cluster

CLUSTER_MAGREF.description: The cluster_magref table provides the magnitude reference ev ent for the cluster. This reference event will be used in de termining the relative magnitude of new events found using t he SSD. Each cluster will need a magnitude reference event t o make a relative magnitude calculation on events identified by the SSD. If the magnitude reference event was not seen a t a refsta we will be unable to perform a relative magnitude calculation for that refsta.

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

MVALUE.comment: Amplitude measurement value (only required for specific mtype(s))

FILTERID.comment: Filter identifier that links to the butterworth filter table

LEAD.comment: Number of seconds before preferred phase for amplitude measurement

DURATION.comment: Total number of seconds of the waveform around the preferred phase for amplitude measurement

CLUSTER_MEC.description: The cluster_mec table provides the location correction infor mation for a sta (element). This information is used to refi ne the locations of origins. The flat file database (fdb) th at is imported into this table should not include commented lines. The cluster_mec's format is the current output of jhd sat. It will have to be augmented by the addition of clustai d when it is imported into a US NDC cluster_mec table. This will make it possible to distinguish between two different e vent clusters for the same station.

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

ONDATE.comment: Julian date that the correction is good from

OFFDATE.comment: Julian date that the correction is good to

TOTAL_EVENTS.comment: Total events used to create the MEC

CLUSTER_ORID.description: The cluster_orid table provides the cluster to orid mapping.

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

CLUSTER_OVERRIDE.description: The cluster_override table contains Multiple Event Analysis (MEA) parameter file overrides for historical purposes. This table is populated when a new cluster version is pushed int o the NDC database with the previous override values.

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

SSD_DIMENSION.comment: Specifies how many SVD dimensions to use in the SVDDISC table.

SVD_LEAD.comment: The number of seconds from the start to the first phase of the waveforms used to generate the svds

MIN_DETECTION_INTERVAL.comment: This value is multiplied by the data's sample rate to determine the MEA detection window size.

LEAD.comment: Number of seconds preceding phase that makes up the reference waveform

LAG.comment: Number of seconds following preferred phase that makes up the reference waveform

BEST_EVENT_MATCH_MULTIPLE.comment: This value is multiplied by a MEA detection window to extend the window to perform correlation to find the best event match.

PHASE_ONSET_MULTIPLE.comment: This value is multiplied by the phase's lead and lag duration to create a window to perform correlation to refine phase onset time.

DET_TRACE_TRIM_MULTIPLE.comment: The value is multiplied by the length of one SVD to define how much to trim from both ends of a detection statistic trace.

CHANNEL_MASKING_THRESHOLD.comment: The proportion of a channel that can be masked before the channel is removed from the threshold calculation

PHASE_SPECIFIC_OVERRIDE_REC.comment: Name of the phase override recipe to use ('-' value represents no override desired).

MAX_DELAZ.comment: Allowable difference between suspect azimuth and sta-cluster azimuth seconds per kilometer

MAX_DELSLOW.comment: Allowable difference between suspect slowness and ref slowness seconds per kilometer

CLUSTER_PHASE_OVERRIDE.description: The cluster_phase_override table contains Multiple Event Ana lysis (MEA) parameter file overrides for historical purposes . This table is populated when a new cluster version is push ed into the NDC database with the previous override values.

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated.

PHASE_SPECIFIC_OVERRIDE_REC.comment: Name of the phase override recipe to use ('-' -> >value represents no override desired).

LEAD.comment: Number of seconds preceding phase that makes up the reference waveform.

LAG.comment: Number of seconds following preferred phase that makes up the reference waveform.

MAXADJ.comment: The maximum time in seconds that a phase can be adjusted.

CLUSTER_STATION.description: The cluster_station table is used to store station-specific (not element-specific) information, e.g., stations used in c luster, azimuth limits, slowness limits.

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

STA.comment: Station to which array elements are referenced; used to identify sites to include in cluster

MAX_DELAZ.comment: Allowable difference between suspect azimuth and sta-cluster azimuth seconds per kilometer

MAX_DELSLOW.comment: Allowable difference between suspect slowness and ref slowness seconds per kilometer

SSD_DIMENSION.comment: Number of subspace vectors to include for sta/chan processing

SVD_LEAD.comment: The number of seconds from the start to the first phase of the waveforms used to generate the svds

SVD_LAG.comment: The number of seconds from the start to the first phase of the waveforms used to generate the svds

LEAD.comment: Number of seconds preceding phase that makes up the reference waveform

LAG.comment: Number of seconds following preferred phase that makes up the reference waveform

CLUSTER_THRESHOLD.description: The cluster_threshold table provides the threshold informati on for the cluster. It is possible for a cluster to have sev eral different threshold values.

DETECTOR_TYPE.comment: The dector type to use with this threshold (SSD, CORR, AMP)

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

ORID.comment: The orid used to create the threshold if this is a correlation threshold otherwise the value is 0

CHANNEL_MASKING_THRESHOLD.comment: The proportion of a channel that can be masked before the channel is removed from the threshold calculation

CODAMAG_INPUT.description: The codamag_input table contains key input parameters that a re used to calculate coda amplitudes, including the boundari es of the noise and signal windows and the path and site cor rection values.

AMPDEF.comment: d or n flag indicating if station/element is included (d,D) or excluded (n,N) from coda magnitude processing

SAMPRATE.comment: The sample rate of the data corresponding to this record

TIME.comment: Epoch start time of signal window

ENDTIME.comment: Epoch end time of signal window

NOISE_START_TIME.comment: Epoch start time of noise window

NOISE_END_TIME.comment: Epoch end time of noise window

SHAPEDMIN.comment: Minimum 1-D calibration distance for coda decay and spreading

SHAPEDMAX.comment: Maximum 1-D calibration distance for coda decay and spreading

VGDMIN.comment: Minimum 1-D calibration distance for peak velocity

VGDMAX.comment: Maximum 1-D calibration distance for peak velocity

CODAMAG_OUTPUT.description: The codamag_output table contains raw and corrected coda amp litudes for each station/channel/frequency band.

AMPCOR.comment: Amplitude value corrected for path and site

CONTINUOUS_DATA_STATUS.description: A table tracking the SOH indicators embedded in the CD1.1 Da ta Frame

INDICATOR.comment: Status of Health Indicator from the CD1.1 Data Frame

START_DATE.comment: Initial time the indicator was enabled

END_DATE.comment: Last time for which the indicator was enabled

DATAUSER.description: The datauser table tracks authorized users of the Message an d Subscription Subsystems. Each user is identified by a (uni que) username and domain, which must match all e-mail header s. The priority column specifies the class of user, and serv icetime is the last time a request from the user was process ed. Priority and servicetime are considered when selecting t he order in which requests will be processed. The status can either be active or inactive.

USERNAME.comment: User name from the incoming subscription message

DOMAIN.comment: Domain name from the incoming subscription message

EMAILLIMIT.comment: Maximum size of message (in bytes) that will be delivered via e-mail

SERVICETIME.comment: Last time a request from that user was serviced

DA_INTERVAL.description: The da_interval table defines units of processing for data a cquistion . The time, endtime, and name types indicate proce ssing times for a named object. The class type allows a sing le interval table to be used for different classes of object s.

PERCENT_AVAILABLE.comment: Percent of data available in interval

MODDATE.comment: Time of last processing state change

DA_REFSTA_LATENCY.description: The da_refsta_latency table contains latency data for the re ference stations.

DA_REFSTA_SUMMARY.description: Summary of expected percentage of data available for a refer ence station.

PERCENT.comment: Percentage of data available in wfdiscs.

DA_SITECHAN_LATENCY.description: The da_sitechan_latency table contains latency data for the stations and channels.

DECONVOLUTION.description: The deconvolution table provides some of the parameters nece ssary for deconvolution of the instrument response. The inst rument response information for a particular station at a ce rtain time is contained in the sensor and instrument table. The sensor and instrument tables provide the instrument resp onse, type (measured or theoretical), and units. Once the in strument response is removed it will be necessary to convert everything to the same unit.

LOWCUTFRAC.comment: Low cut for cosine filter given as a fraction of lowcutfrac

LOWPASSFREQ.comment: Low cut for cosine filter given as a fraction of lowpassfreq

HIGHCUTFRAC.comment: High cut given as a fraction of Nyquist obtained from nominal sample rate

HIGHPASSFREQ.comment: High cut given as a fraction of Nyquist obtained from nominal sample rate

WATERLEVEL.comment: Limit for division (0.0 means do not apply waterlevel)

FINALUNITS.comment: Final units for the data once the instrument response has been removed (d, v, or a)

DEFINING_OBSTYPES.description: Defines and describes all valid observation types that can b e used as defining for the USNDC.

DEFINING_RULES.description: Provides the rules for when an observation can be defining a nd the appropriate default value to be assigned.

PHASE.comment: Phase restriction for the Defining Rule

ON_DATE.comment: Date the defining rule becomes enabled

OFF_DATE.comment: Date the defining rule becomes disabled

DEFINING_VALUES.description: Defines and describes all valid defining values that can be assigned to an observation type in the USNDC.

DETECTION.description: The detection table contains summary information about wavef orms.

DETECTION_THRESHOLD.description: The detection_threshold table contains the calculated thresh old for the timeframe processed.

DISCRIMUSE.description: The discrimuse table contains the use/nonuse of station data in discriminant voting. It identifies, for each station ass ociated to the origin, the use or non-use of that station's data in the discriminant vote for six different discriminant s. The votes are then combined to determine the overall even t classification (see the discrimvote table).

DISCRIM_FLAG.comment: Discriminant is used in event classification for the origin and station (T,F)

DISCRIMVOTE.description: The discrimvote table identifies the vote value for each of six discriminants (discrimtypes). These votes are combined t o determine the overall event classification. When the vote is overridden, it includes evaluator's comments.

VOTE.comment: Overall vote for the discriminant factor

DISCRIM_PARAM.description: The discrim_param table contains group velocities for each p olyid and station.

LOWCUTFRAC.comment: low frequency cut for instrument correction in Hertz

MINLOWPASSFREQ.comment: low frequency pass for instrument correction in Hertz

HIGHPASSFRAC.comment: high frequency pass for instrument correction in Hertz

HIGHCUTFRAC.comment: high frequency cut for instrument correction in Hertz

PNGV1.comment: beginning group velocity in km/s for Pn phase

PNGV2.comment: ending group velocity in km/s for Pn phase

PNINT.comment: intercept time in seconds for Pg phase

PGGV1.comment: beginning group velocity in km/s for Pg phase

PGGV2.comment: ending group velocity in km/s for Pg phase

PGINT.comment: intercept time in seconds for Pg phase

SNGV1.comment: beginning group velocity in km/s for Sn phase

SNGV2.comment: ending group velocity in km/s for Sn phase

SNINT.comment: intercept time in seconds for Sn phase

LGGV1.comment: beginning group velocity in km/s for Lg phase

LGGV2.comment: ending group velocity in km/s for Lg phase

LGINT.comment: intercept time in seconds for Lg phase

TFACTOR.comment: minimum number of cycles in the window needed to calculate an amplitude

TAPERWIDTH.comment: fraction of waveform to taper at each end

DLMAN.description: The dlman table keeps track of currently running DLMan insta nces. The column machine is the host on which this dlid runs (it may not run elsewhere). The column running indicates wh ether that DLMan is currently operational. The table also pr ovides the ports that this dlid is currently using to listen to other processes.

DOPPLER_DETECTION.description: The doppler_detection table contains summary information abo ut waveforms.

USE_AS_REFERENCE_EVENT.comment: When set to "y", use this event as a reference event for internal AFTAC station tuning process.

INTERNAL_COMMENTS.comment: Comment made by an analyst to leave feedback/questions/observations and tie it to the event without it affecting the Doppler report.

ANALYST.comment: The analyst that created the event report

TIMESENT.comment: Time at which the event report was released

LDDATE.comment: Time at which the detector generated the event

ECM_CHAN_AMPLITUDE.description: The ecm_chan_amplitude table contains time windows (start an d end times), raw amplitude, and MDAC for each orid, station , channel, phase and frequency bin. These measurements are c ombined according to the parameters of the discriminant bein g calculated.

LFREQ.comment: low end of frequency bin used to filter measurement

HFREQ.comment: high end of frequency bin used to filter measurement

AMPCOR_VERID.comment: AmpCor version Identifier used in ECM Versioning

NTIME.comment: start time of the noise window

NENDTIME.comment: end time of the noise window

AMPDEF.comment: Defining flag for element amplitude measurement to be used for station/network average

ECM_CONSTANT.description: The ecm_constant table contains calibration constants for EC M. This table is for lone constants that are not dependant on which channel, phase, station, or polyid being looked at.

ECM_COV.description: The ecm_cov table contains a covariance for each polyid, sou rce type, and pair of discriminants. All records with the s ame polyid and source type will combine to define a single c ovariance matrix used for combining discriminants.

COV_VERID.comment: version identifier of the covariance matrix

COVARIANCE.comment: covariance of these two discriminants for this source type within this region of interest

MEAN_1.comment: mean value of the first discriminant

ECM_DISCRIMINANTS.description: The ecm_discriminants table contains p-values for each evid and discriminant name.

COV_VERID.comment: version identifier of the covariance matrix

DISCRIM_P_VALUE.comment: p-value of this discriminant for this reference event

EXPLANATION.comment: text explanation of how this discriminant was calculated

ECM_EVENT_RESULTS.description: The ecm_event_results table contains the classification for each event.

EVID.comment: id of the event of interest

COV_VERID.comment: version identifier of the covariance matrix

CLASS_TYPE.comment: source type as determined by ECM

CLASS_TYPE_OVRD.comment: source type as overridden by an analyst

ECM_REF_CHAN_AMPLITUDE.description: The ecm_ref_chan_amplitude table contains reference time win dows (start and end times), raw amplitude, and MDAC for each evid, station, channel, phase and frequency bin. These meas urements were combined according to the parameters of the di scriminant that was calculated.

LFREQ.comment: low end of frequency bin used to filter measurement

HFREQ.comment: high end of frequency bin used to filter measurement

AMPCOR_VERID.comment: AmpCor version Identifier used in ECM Versioning

NTIME.comment: start time of the noise window

NENDTIME.comment: end time of the noise window

AMPDEF.comment: Defining flag for element amplitude measurement to be used for station/network average

ECM_REF_DISCRIM.description: The ecm_ref_discrim table contains a p-value for each refid and discriminant. The refid relates to a specific reference event in the ecm_ref_event.

COV_VERID.comment: version identifier of the covariance matrix

DISCRIM_P_VALUE.comment: p-value of this discriminant for this reference event

ECM_REF_EVENT.description: The ecm_ref_event table contains event data for each event u sed to calibrate the ECM.

MB.comment: body wave magnitude of reference event

MS.comment: surface wave magnitude of reference event

COV_VERID.comment: version identifier of the covariance matrix

ECM_SOURCES.description: The ecm_sources table contains aggregate p-values and poster iori probabilities for each evid and source type.

COV_VERID.comment: version identifier of the covariance matrix

ENVELOPE_CONTRIBUTION.description: The envelope_contribution table contains information as to w hich frequency bands are defining or nondefining for coda ma gnitude calculation. Bands may be set defining or nondefinin g either automatically by DFX or manually by an analyst.

AMPDEF.comment: d or n flag indicating if station/element is included (d,D) or excluded (n,N) from coda magnitude processing

EVENT.description: The event table contains a list of events. Multiple origins may be defined for any one event. The column prefor points t o the preferred origin.

EVENT_CONTROL.description: The event_control table contains event location and magnitud e control parameters. This information acts as an archive of the specific user-defined controls that were used to determ ine the location and magnitude of a given orid. The table al so includes two measurement columns (cov_sm_axes and cov_dep th_time) that allow the coverage ellipse to be determined fr om the confidence ellipse axes.

LOC_SRC_DPNT_REG.comment: Region name of source-dependent location correction

LOC_SDV_SCREEN.comment: Flag to ignore large data residuals in location

LOC_ALPHA_ONLY.comment: Flag to use only primary stations in location

LOC_ALL_STAS.comment: Flag to use only stations with src_dpnt_corr

LOC_DIST_VARWGT.comment: Flag to use distance variance weighting

MAG_SRC_DPNT_REG.comment: Region name of source-dependent magnitude correction

MAG_SDV_SCREEN.comment: Flag to ignore large magnitude data residuals

MAG_ALPHA_ONLY.comment: Flag to limit station net used in magnitude

MAG_ALL_STAS.comment: Flag to use only primary stations in magnitude

EVENT_CORRELATION.description: The event_Correlation table containts correlations between s ource events in the NDC operational database to reference ev ents in the NDC archive databases for time periods as great as 15 years.

SOURCE_ORID.comment: The source origin used in the event correlation.

SOURCE_EVID.comment: The source event used in the event correlation.

SOURCE_STARTTIME.comment: The start time of the source waveform segment used for correlation.

SOURCE_SECS.comment: The length of the source waveform in seconds used for correlation.

REFERENCE_ORID.comment: The reference origin for this correlation from the archive database.

REFERENCE_EVID.comment: The reference event for this correlation from the archive database.

REFERENCE_STARTTIME.comment: The start time of the reference waveform segment used for correlation.

REFERENCE_SECS.comment: The length of the reference waveform in seconds used for correlation.

FILTER_STRING.comment: Compact filter representation used as parameter to filter_data_by_string module.

CHAN_LIST.comment: List of channels used for array correlation

CORR_COEF.comment: Correlation coefficient used in this correlation calculation.

SCAN_TYPE.comment: Correlation Scan type: AUTO, USER, or REF.

EVENT_QUALITY.description: The event_quality table holds the event quality attributes t hat are calculated by various processes such as EvLoc, ARS, and GAConflict using the Event Quality Generator.

NSMAJAX.comment: Normalized semi-major axis of error ellipse

NDELTA_STA.comment: Normalized distance to the closest station

FEEDBACK.description: The feedback table contains analyst feedback from one analys t regarding a discrepancy made by another analyst' work in t he Analyst Review System (ARS).

EVENT_TIME.comment: Epoch time that the event occurred.

ANALYST.comment: The targeted analyst the feedback pertains to.

ACCOUNT.comment: Pipeline account that the analyst is receiving feedback for.

FEEDBACK_ANALYST.comment: The original analyst of the event being reviewed.

FEEDBACK_ACCOUNT.comment: Pipeline account from which the analyst is receiving feedback.

RESPONSE.comment: This is the response by the analyst to the given feedback. If the feedback is rejected, this is where the reason for rejection should be documented. Rejection is used to allow accurate trending of fe edback

FEEDBACK_CATAFFILIATION.description: The feedback_cataffiliation contains foregin keys to the fee dback table and feedback_categories table to assign categori cal affiliation(s) to each feedback.

FEEDBACK_CATEGORIES.description: The feedback_categories table contains descriptions of each feedback category referenced by the feedback_cataffiliation table.

TITLE.comment: Short description/title of the feedback category

DESCRIPTION.comment: Detailed description of the feedback category

FEEDBACK_SCREENSHOTS.description: The feedback_screenshots table contains image files related to feedback entries.

TYPE.comment: Screenshot image file type (Initial allowable types (jpg, jpeg, png))

FEEDBACK_STATE.description: The feedback_state table contains one or more states a feedb ack is currently in or has formerly been in. A Feedback entr y can only be in one state at a time, such as saved or rejec ted. As a feedback progresses through its lifecycle, it will have more than one state per feedback entry, and the latest one entered in this table will always be the current state.

FEEDBACK_STATE_CATEGORIES.description: The feedback_state_category contains descriptions of the var ious states a feedback record can be in such as saved or rej ected.

TITLE.comment: Short description/title of the feedback state category

DESCRIPTION.comment: Detailed description of the feedback state category

AUTHOR.comment: The analyst creating the feedback state category.

FILTER.description: The filter table will contain the core information needed to identify filters. The attributes in this table will be high ly indexed for fast searching. The attributes will allow app lication to quickly access enough information to 1) determin e the type of filter so that an application can branch accor dingly to efficiently handle loading or 2) determine uniquen ess when assessing if a filter does or does not exist.

FILTERID.comment: Identifier for a filter or filter collection.

FILTER_METHOD.comment: Filter algorithm family. [Cascade, AR, Butterworth, Phase_Matched, Digital, Dynamic, etc.]

FILTER_STRING.comment: Compact filter representation used as parameter to filter_data_by_string module.

FILTER_HASH.comment: Standardized filter specification, formatted for uniqueness checking and fast access.

FILTER_COEFFICIENTS.description: The filter_coefficients table contains a collection of doubl e precision coefficients for a filter. For the persistent pa rameters bundle, the filter_coefficients table will be used to store numerator and denominator coefficients for a coeffi cient configured filter, identified by a parent record in th e filter table.

FILTER_GROUP.description: The filter_group table is used to link together the individu al filters of a compound filter. The parent filter record of a compound filter will have a compound_filter indicator val ue of 'Y' and may have a filter method of 'Cascade' or 'AR'. The filter_group table will contain one record for each fil ter in the compound filter group, all sharing a common paren t filter record. For Flexibility, the key to the record is p arent_filterid-child_filterid-child_sequence, to allow compl ex compound filters to use a filter more than once.

PARENT_FILTERID.comment: Identifier for a collection or group of filters.

CHILD_FILTERID.comment: Identifier for a simple / single filter.

CHILD_SEQUENCE.comment: Order that the child filter should be applied.

FILTER_VALUES_DOUBLE.description: The filter_values_double table will store filter parameters and metadata (float values). Each record will contain only o ne piece of information. Each filter type will store only th ose pieces of information that are pertinent to that filter type. A butterworth filter will have fhi and flo attribute r ecords while digital filters may have num_numerator_coeffs o r compute_time_shift attributes.

FILTER_VALUES_INTEGER.description: The filter_values_double table will store filter parameters and metadata (integer values). Each record will contain only one piece of information. Each filter type will store only those pieces of information that are pertinent to that filte r type. A butterworth filter will have fhi and flo attribute records while digital filters may have num_numerator_coeffs or compute_time_shift attributes.

FILTER_VALUES_STRING.description: The filter_values_string table will store filter parameters and metadata (string values). Each record will contain only one piece of information. Each filter type will store only those pieces of information that are pertinent to that filte r type. A butterworth filter will have fhi and flo attribute records while digital filters may have num_numerator_coeffs or compute_time_shift attributes.

FK_PROCESSING.description: The fk_processing table contains identifiers to link paramet ers for fk processing. It provides an override of the defaul t processing for a station and phase. This override is speci fied on a per arrival basis.

PROCID.comment: ID number of a set of waveform processing parameters

LEAD.comment: Number of seconds before phase to include in processing

LAG.comment: Number of seconds after phase to include in processing

FTPFAILED.description: The ftpfailed table facilitates ftp retrieval and the placem ent of data messages between contributing systems.

FTPSTATUS.comment: Status of ftp attempt (retry or failed)

FTPLOGIN.description: The ftplogin table is used by the auxiliary data retrieval s ystem to obtain data via ftp from auxiliary stations.

GA_TAG.description: The ga_tag table contains information on the use of arrivals and origins in the GA application.

OBJTYPE.comment: Type of identifier (a for arrival, o for origin)

EVID_REJECT.comment: Evid of origin arrival was rejected from

GREGION.description: The gregion table contains geographic region numbers and the ir equivalent descriptions.

HISTORIC_INFO_CYLINDER.description: The historic_info_cylinder table is used to describe the cyl inder (ga_grid) in a shell.

HISTORIC_INFO_SHELL.description: The historic_info_shell table is used to describe the shell containing cylinders for specific station and phase.

RELIABILITY.comment: Estimate based on percent of events observed

PROCESSING_MODE.comment: Defines the type of processing used to determine the shell

ON_DATE.comment: The date the historic information shell first became active or was created

OFF_DATE.comment: The date the historic information shell was removed from the system or made obsolete

HISTORIC_INFO_STA_PHASE.description: The historic_info_sta_phase table describes the station and phase information for a given time used to compute the histo ric cylinders and shells.

HISTORIC_INFO_STA_PHASE_ID.comment: Historic information for stations and phases identifier

RELIABILITY.comment: Estimate based on percent of events observed

PROCESSING_MODE.comment: Defines the type of processing used for the station/phase pair

ON_DATE.comment: The date the historic information station and phase first became active or was created

OFF_DATE.comment: The date the historic information station and phase was removed from the sysem or made obsolete

HYDRO_ARRIVAL.description: The hydro_arrival table contains hydroacoustic arrival infor mation such as duration and the crossing point lag of the si gnal, autocorrelation bubble pulse frequency, autocovariance peak ratio (rt), cepstrum bubble pulse, bubble pulse amplit ude versus root mean square (rms), filter ratio, normalized amplitude, sensor yield, and sensor yield error.

CPLAG.comment: Crossing point lag of the signal

AMPCORCLIP.comment: Correction to raw amplitude for clipping

AMPCORDIST.comment: Correction to raw amplitude for distance

AMPCORDEPTH.comment: Correction to raw amp for depth

HYDRO_ARR_GROUP.description: The hydro_arr_group table contains hydroacoustic arrival-bas ed estimates of slowness and azimuth.

HYDRO_ASSOC.description: The hydro_assoc table contains the azimuth contribution info rmation for an arrival that is connected to a particular hyd ro arrival group.

HYDRO_ORIGIN.description: The hydro_origin table contains a summary of AFTAC-specific hydroacoustic origin information such as Type of origin loca tion, determined from: Seismic system. Various unique hydroa coustic signal types, volcanic underwater, or undetermined. Bubble pulse frequency used to calculate the yield value and that yield value error. This table also identifies if this origin is part of a series and the unique identifier for tha t series.

INSTRUMENT.description: The instrument table contains ancillary calibration informat ion. It holds nominal one-frequency calibration factors for each instrument and pointers to nominal frequency-dependent calibration for an instrument. This table also holds pointer s to the exact calibrations obtained by direct measurement o n a particular instrument (see sensor).

INTERVAL.description: The interval table defines units of processing. The time, en dtime, and name types indicate processing times for a named object. The class type allows a single interval table to be used for different classes of objects.

PERCENT_AVAILABLE.comment: Percent of data available in interval

MODDATE.comment: Time of last processing state change

MDAC_FD.description: The mdac_fd table contains frequency dependent MDAC paramete rs for each corrid, frequency, and channel. (corrid is an in ternal id that relates to an mdac_fi record which is depende nt on polyid, phase, and station.)

MDAC_FI.description: The mdac_fi table contains frequency independent MDAC parame ters for each polyid, phase, and station.

ZETA.comment: Ratio of P and S wave corner frequencies

M0_REF.comment: Reference seismic moment used with psi in Nm

DISTCRIT.comment: Critical distance for geometric spreading function in meters

ALPHAS.comment: P velocity at the source in m/s

BETAS.comment: S velocity at the source in m/s

RHOS.comment: Density at the source in kg/m3

ALPHAR.comment: P velocity at the receiver in m/s

BETAR.comment: S velocity at the receiver in m/s

RHOR.comment: Density at the receiver in kg/m3

RADPATP.comment: Radiation pattern excitation factor for P waves

RADPATS.comment: Radiation pattern excitation factor for S waves

SNR1.comment: Minimum signal-to-noise ratio used to select spectral amplitudes

SNR2.comment: Minimum signal-to-noise for applying MDAC parameters

NOISETYPE.comment: Noise identifier e.g. pre-event or pre-phase

MSGAUX.description: The msgaux table contains records of unsuccessfully processe d Automatic Data Request Manager (AutoDRM) messages.

COMMAND.comment: Command that could not be processed

MSGDATATYPE.description: The msgdatatype table supports data tracking by recording ea ch data section in a message for incoming and outgoing messa ges.

MSGDTYPE.comment: Data type of the data section within the message

MSGDFORMAT.comment: General format of data that follows

FOFF.comment: File offset to beginning of data section

MSGDEST.description: The msgdest table contains information about messages sent.

TRANSMETH.comment: Method by which the response is to be delivered to the requester

MSGSTATUS.comment: Current status of the response message

ITIME.comment: Time at which table entry was made

TIMESENT.comment: Time at which message was sent

MSGDISC.description: The msgdisc table contains information pertinent to messages including the date and time that the message was sent or re ceived, identification information, and where the message is stored.

EXTMSGID.comment: Message identification string provided by the sender

INTID.comment: Either the locally generated msgid of an earlier table entry that evoked the creation of this table entry or the reqid from the request table of an internally generated request

FOFF.comment: Byte offset of data segment within file

MFOFF.comment: Offset in bytes to beginning of message

FILEOFF.comment: Number of bytes to the first character of the e-mail file (first character of the e-mail header)

MSVMAX_DESCRIPT.description: The msvmax_descript is the child of arrival and amplitude ta bles. It is the parent of the msvmax_results table.

HIGH_SNR_COUNT.comment: Count of periods where noise is greater than signal

MSVMAX_RESULTS.description: The msvmax_results table is the child of the msvmax_descript table.

AMPCOR.comment: Amplitude value corrected for Airy phase Butterworth filter

TIME.comment: Epoch start time of signal window

ENDTIME.comment: Epoch start time of signal window

NETMAG.description: The netmag table contain estimates of network magnitudes of different types for an event. Each network magnitude has a u nique magid. Station magnitudes used to compute the network magnitude are in the stamag table.

NETWORK.description: The network table contains general information about seismic networks (see affiliation).

ON_DATE.comment: The date the network first became active or was created

OFF_DATE.comment: The date the network was removed from the system or made obsolete

NETYIELD.description: The netyield table contains network-wide yield values obtain ed from the yield values at all available stations for an ev ent.

NET_CODA_SPECTRUM.description: The net_coda_spectrum table contains the theoretical source spectrum for an event, used to obtain the network moment mag nitude values. The theoretical spectrum is fit to the observ ed spectrum in all frequency bands for a station that are se t to defining in the envelope_contribution table.

AMPCOR.comment: Amplitude value corrected for path and site

OMITTED_CHANNELS.description: The omitted_channels table identifies time intervals for whi ch channel masks exist. Channel masks are used to exclude wa veform data for the specified station, channel, time and end time from interactive and automatic data processing due to d ata quality problems (timing, calibration, etc.).

TIME.comment: Epoch time for start of channel omitted

ENDTIME.comment: Epoch time for end of channel omitted

ORIGERR.description: The origerr table contains summaries of confidence bounds in origin estimations. The origerr_ga table is used by the GA application to store temporary origin error information. The measurement types are the elements of the location covarian ce matrix. The descriptive types give the uncertainties in l ocation, depth, and origin time. These quantities are calcul ated from the covariance matrix, assuming gaussian errors an d a confidence level conf.

ORIGERR_GA.description: The origerr table contains summaries of confidence bounds in origin estimations. The origerr_ga table is used by the GA application to store temporary origin error information. The measurement types are the elements of the location covarian ce matrix. The descriptive types give the uncertainties in l ocation, depth, and origin time. These quantities are calcul ated from the covariance matrix, assuming gaussian errors an d a confidence level conf.

ORIGERR_GA_DEL.description: The origerr_ga_del table contains summaries of confidence bo unds in origin estimations.

ORIGIN.description: The origin tables contain information describing a derived o r reported origin for a particular event.

ORIGIN_GA.description: The origin and origin_ga tables contain information describi ng a derived or reported origin for a particular event.

ORIGIN_GA_DEL.description: The origin_ga_del table contains information describing a de rived or reported origin for a particular event that was del eted and may be needed for later reference.

ORIGIN_MEA_TRACE.description: The origin_mea_trace table contains important information ne cessary to trace the subspace detection.

ACTIVETIME_LOOKUP.comment: The time used to lookup the epoch time a cluster was activated. This value is either the application data start time or set to the value of 'cluster-active-time-override' parameter.

ORIGIN_SDO.description: The origin_sdo table contains the point geometry, coverage e llipse polygon, confidence ellipse polygon for an origin.

ORIGIN_TAG.description: The origin_tag table contains information to indicate which mode was used to generate the origin (i.e. automated process ing mode of defining arrivals for an automated event or anal ysis mode for a reviewed event).

PROCESS_MODE.comment: Automated processing mode of defining arrivals or analysis mode

PROCESS_ATTRIBUTE.comment: Additional information to augment the process_mode (e.g. specific spotlight)

NDEF.comment: Number of defining arrivals for automated processing mode

OUTAGE_STATION_DATA.description: The outage_station_data table provides tracking of station a vailability.

OUTAGE_STATION_RECEIVE.description: The outage_station_receive table provides tracking of pipeli ne availability for both the operational and alternate US ND C systems.

POLYGON.description: The polygon table contains the name for each polyid.

POLYPOINT.description: The polypoint table contains a polyid, sequence number, lati tude, and longitude for each point of a polygon. All record s with the same polyid will combine to define a single polyg on.

PROCESSING_RECIPE.description: The processing_recipe table provides the types of waveform p rocessing and the order in which they should be applied. Thi s table allows each cluster station to be processed in diffe rent ways for different proctypes (SVD, CORR, and AMP).

PROCID.comment: ID of the processing recipe. This ID and the procorder form the primary key

PROCMETHOD.comment: Method of processing (taper, deconvolution, butterworth_filter, etc)

IDNAME.comment: The name of the id field (taperid, filterid, etc)

IDVALUE.comment: The value of the id field

PROCORDER.comment: The value of the id field

PROCESS_TRACKING.description: The process_tracking table provides tracking of pipeline ava ilability for both the operational and alternate systems.

QCMASKDEF.description: The qcmaskdef table contains information defining the parame ters that went into the calculation of the QC mask.

FIX.comment: Flag indicating how to fix the bad segment

NTAPER.comment: Number of points to taper outside segment of length >=drop_thr

DROP_THR.comment: Number of consecutive equal-valued samples to call a bad segment

SINGLE_TRACE_SPIKE_THR.comment: Amplitude ratio threshold for single-point spikes

NITER.comment: Number of iterations to perform extended QC

NSAMP.comment: Number of samples in a time interval for extended QC

NOVER.comment: Number of overlap samples for extended QC

SPIKE_THR.comment: Amplitude ratio threshold for extended QC spikes

SPIKE_STAT.comment: Flag for statistic to use for spike detection across multiple data vectors

SPIKE_NPWIN.comment: Number of points to use for single vector extended QC spike detection

SPIKE_DSET.comment: Flag for data set to use for extended QC across multiple data vectors

SPIKE_WINLEN.comment: Number of samples used in single-trace QC

INTERQUAR_COEF.comment: Inter-quartile range multiplier for single-trace QC

NOISE_NSAMP.comment: Number of samples in averaging window for noisy channel processing

NOISE_NOVERLAP.comment: Number of samples windows overlap for noisy channel processing

ALGORITHM_LIST.comment: List of algorithms applied during QC processing

ONDATE.comment: The date this record starts to be used

OFFDATE.comment: The date this record is no longer used

QCMASKINFO.description: The qcmaskinfo table contains QC mask data information about a channel and time interval for which QC processing was per formed.

NSEG.comment: The number of segments for this mask ( see qcmaskseg table )

QCMASKSEG.description: The qcmaskseg table contains information about masked data s egments resulting from QC processing.

MASKTYPE.comment: Flag indicating type of mask for a given segment

QSHELL_INTERVAL.description: The qshell_interval table records processing that was perfor med against interval table rows. It records the start and e nd dates of execution of each process name in the processing sequence for the interval class.

MODDATE.comment: Time of last processing state change

RDA_PARAM.description: The rda_param table contains the Regularized Discrimination Analysis (RDA) parameters for each polyid.

REG_RATIO_DISCRIM.description: The reg_ratio_discrim table contains variances and means for each polyid, numerator phase and frequency, and denominator phase and frequency. These parameters are used for discrim inants which are ratios of two phases.

COV_VERID.comment: version identifier of the covariance matrix

NUM_LOW_FREQ.comment: Low end of frequency band used to filter numerator measurement

NUM_HI_FREQ.comment: High end of frequency band used to filter numerator measurement

DEN_LOW_FREQ.comment: Low end of frequency band used to filter denominator measurement

DEN_HI_FREQ.comment: High end of frequency band used to filter denominator measurement

MEAN_EX_VAL.comment: Mean p-value for explosions for this discriminant within this region

NUM_STATION_VAR.comment: Variability due to station in the numerator phase

DEN_STATION_VAR.comment: Variability due to station in the denominator phase

NUM_EVENT_VAR.comment: Variability due to event in the numerator phase

DEN_EVENT_VAR.comment: Variability due to event in the denominator phase

LDDATE.comment: Date this parameter set was loaded

REMARK.description: The remark table contains comments. This table may be used t o store free-form comments that embellish records of other t ables. The commid type in many tables refers to a record in the remark table. If commid is NA (1) in a record of any oth er table, no comments are stored for that record.

REMOVED_BEAM_DFILE.description: This table contains a list of beam files that have been remo ved from the USNDC. It is used to clean up orphaned beam fil es on the non-mission system side since they are only remove d on the mission side.

REQUEST.description: The request table defines segments of auxiliary waveform dat a to be acquired. The time, endtime, sta, and chan types def ine a single unit of data. Data import programs must succeed in acquiring all the data for a time interval before changi ng the state to indicate success.

TIME.comment: Starting time of requested waveform data

ENDTIME.comment: Ending time of requested waveform data

STATECOUNT.comment: Number of failed attempts (when state = failed)

MODTIME.comment: Time of last state change (epoch time)

SADO_EMAIL_HISTORY.description: The SADO table contains the email history of reports sent by users using the SADO Tool.

SADO_PDF_REPORTS.description: The SADO table contains the binary stored pdf reports and as sociated id numbers.

AUTHOR.comment: Author of the SADO PDF Report.

SADO_REPORT.description: The SADO table contains data about the SADO report and the e vent for the report.

TITLE.comment: Title of the report. Combination of the evid number and date and timestamp of the report

ANALYST.comment: The analyst that created the event of the report

ACCOUNT.comment: Pipeline account the report is being written from

CLASSIFICATION.comment: The classification of the report material

TTGE.comment: Boolean indicating the Alert Manager sent an email for this report

SADO_RELEASED.comment: Boolean indicating the SADO report has been released to the AFTAC website

ALERT_MANAGER_CALLED.comment: Boolean indicating if the user called the alert manager

EXERCISE.comment: Boolean indicating if the report is an exercise report

EMAIL_TYPE.comment: Indicates the report type of type 0, 1, or 2

ALERT_MANAGER.comment: Indicates which alert manager was called if an alert manager was called

YIELD_CALCULATOR_REGION_SELECT.comment: Region selected for chemical and yield calculator.

FINAL_DETERMINATION.comment: SADO final determination of the event

MAG_MAGTYPE.comment: String variable of magnitude + magtype used for magtypes selection in SADO tool.

OVERBURDEN_SET.comment: Boolean value indicating if the user set the depth of burial manually.

OVERBURDEN.comment: Manually set Depth of Burial in meters.

COMMENTS.comment: Commentary section for the SADO to write any extra information they would like to include in report.

ECM_DETERMINATION.comment: ECM determination selected by the user

SADO_REPORT_LANDMARKS.description: The SADO table contains landmarks and information about land marks related to the event

TESTSITE.comment: Boolean indicating if the landmark is a testsite from the testsite table

NAME.comment: Name for the landmark. If it is a testsite, it is the testsite name. If it is user added, it is the name provided by the user.

DISTANCE.comment: Distance of landmark from event location in degrees.

AUTHOR.comment: Author of this SADO Report Landmark

SADO_SCREENSHOTS.description: The SADO table contains image files related to SADO reports

TYPE.comment: Screenshot image file types (Initial allowable types (jpg, jpeg, png))

SADO_STATE.description: The SADO table contains the current state of the reports. T he reports can be new, saved, submitted, or modified.

SADO_STATE_CATEGORIES.description: The SADO table contains descriptions of the various states a report can be in.

TITLE.comment: Short description/title of the sado report category

AUTHOR.comment: Author of this SADO State Category

SADO_USERS.description: The SADO_USERS table contains the first and last name of the SADO to be used for and appear in SADO reports.

SADO_NAME.comment: First and last name of the SADO.

SENSOR.description: The sensor table contains calibration information for specif ic sensor channels. This table provides a record of updates in the calibration factor or clock error of each instrument and links a sta/chan/time to a complete instrument response in the instrument table. Waveform data are converted into ph ysical units through multiplication by the calib type locate d in wfdisc. The correct value of calib may not be accuratel y known when the wfdisc record is entered into the database. The sensor table provides the mechanism (calratio and calpe r) to update calib, without requiring possibly hundreds of w fdisc records to be updated. Through the foreign key inid, t his table is linked to instrument, which has types pointing to flat files holding detailed calibration information in a variety of formats (see instrument).

TIME.comment: Epoch time of start of recording period

ENDTIME.comment: Epoch time of end of recording period

SITE.description: The site table contains station location information. It nam es and describes a point on the earth where measurements are made (e.g., the location of an instrument or array of instr uments). This table contains information that normally chang es infrequently, such as location. In addition, the site tab le contains types that describe the offset of a station rela tive to an array reference location. Global data integrity i mplies that the sta/ondate in site be consistent with the st a/chan/ondate in the sitechan table.

SITEAUX.description: The siteaux table contains additional site-dependent paramet ers that are not included in the site table.

SITECHAN.description: The sitechan table contains station-channel information. It describes the orientation of a recording channel at the site referenced by sta. The table provides information about the various channels that are available at a station and mainta ins a record of the physical channel configuration at a site .

SNR_PHASE.description: The snr_phase table contains the minimum number of stations and signal-to-noise ratio needed to measure each phase in ea ch region for each station and channel. These parameters ar e used for discriminants which are ratios of two phases.

SREGION.description: The sregion table contains seismic region numbers and their equivalent descriptions.

STAMAG.description: The stamag table contains station magnitude estimates based upon measurements made on specific seismic phases. Values in the stamag table are used to calculate network magnitudes s tored in the netmag table.

MAGDEF.comment: flag indicating if magnitude is defining (d,D) or nondefining (n,N,x,X)

STANET.description: The stanet table is used for Distributed Processing. It cont ains station to array mapping.

TIME.comment: Starting time for station in network

STAQUAL_DNAMES.description: The staqual_dnames table contains reference data of the Stat ion and the associated detection beam for use with staqual_d aily_summary table to determine which dname is used for a pa rticular station quality measurement.

ON_TIME.comment: Epoch time when a station was turned on

OFF_TIME.comment: Epoch time when a station was or will be turned off

STATION_PROCESSING.description: The station_processing table provides a link between the sta tion and the cluster and the processing recipe for that proc essing type.

CLUSTAID.comment: ID number of a cluster and refsta combination

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

PROCTYPE.comment: The type of processing (ex: SVD, AMP, Corr)

STATION_QUALITY.description: The station_quality table holds station quality attributes c alculated and stored by DFX.

EXPECTED.comment: Expected number of seconds of data for segment

RETRIEVED.comment: Actual number of seconds of data for a segment

MASKED.comment: Number of seconds masked in segment

NOISEDEV.comment: Estimate of variability in noise level for the segment

NOISETYPE.comment: mean-sd; noise=power beam mean; noisedev=standard deviation; med-mad; noise=power beam median; noisedev=median absolute deviation

STAYIELD.description: The stayield table contains yield values calculated from cod a amplitudes obtained for a single station.

STA_CODA_SPECTRUM.description: The sta_coda_spectrum table contains the theoretical source spectrum for an event, used to obtain the station moment mag nitude values. The theoretical spectrum is fit to the observ ed spectrum in all frequency bands for a station that are se t to defining in the envelope_contribution table.

AMPCOR.comment: Amplitude value corrected for path and site

SVDDISC.description: The svddisc table contains a left singular vector (LSV) head er file and descriptive information. This table provides a p ointer (or index) to singular value decompositions stored on disk. The LSVs are stored in ordinary disk files called svd disc or '.lsv' files as a sequence of binary four byte float values.

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

UNITS.comment: Units of waveform used to create LSV

FOFF.comment: Byte offset of data segment within file

SVDDISC_CHAN_ORDER.description: The svddisc_chan_order table contains the order in which the sta and chans were combined together to form the input sent to the SVD. This is the order in which the sta and chans ar e passed to the SVD must be the same as the order of the sta and chans of the observed data passed to the SVD.

CLUSTAID.comment: ID of the Cluster and Station

ACTIVETIME.comment: The epochtime a cluster was activated

TAPER.description: The taper table contains processing parameter.

TAPERID.comment: ID number of a taper processing parameter

TAPER_TYPE.comment: Type of tapering to be applied during filtering

TAPER_PERCT.comment: Percent of points to be tapered

TIMESTAMP.description: The timestamp table is used by automated processing to recor d time milestones associated with time-series data.

TOMO_INFO.description: The tomo_info table contains pointers to the storage locatio n of the tomography grids used by coda magnitude processing to obtain the path correction values.

USER_FILTER.description: The user_filter table is used to store the list of filters d esignated by a user to be their filter selection list option s.

SEQ.comment: Order that the filter will be displayed in the list.

FILTER_STRING.comment: Compact filter representation used as parameter to filter_data_by_string module.

USER_PRIVILEGES.description: This table lists the users who are allowed to apply channel masks to waveform data and the maximum time duration each us er can apply a channel mask (applies to omitted_channels tab le). This table also lists the users who are allowed to appl y nondefining location and magnitude indicators (timedef, az def, slodef and magdef) without respect to time duration (ap plies to nondefining table).

APP_TABLE.comment: Table that this authorization applies to

WFACTIVITY.description: The wfactivity table describes activity in the wfdisc table for a channel group and time region.

DURATION.comment: Duration in seconds of the time region

MIN_TIME.comment: Minimum time found in wfdisc for the time period

MAX_ENDTIME.comment: Maximum endtime found in wfdisc for the time period

MODDATE.comment: Time of last processing state change

WFAUDIT.description: The wfaudit table contains records describing the sequences of changes made to rows in the wfdisc table for continuous ( raw) waveform data

OLD_TIME.comment: :old.time value provided to the wfdisc trigger

NEW_TIME.comment: :new.time value provided to the wfdisc trigger

MODDATE.comment: Time of last processing state change

WFCONV.description: The wfconv table contains data translations that are to be p erformed on incoming data before they are written to disk by the DLMan application. Data compression types include "-" i f the data is not compressed or "CA" for Canadian compressio n. "Type" in columns intype and outtype is the fixed-width d ata type (e.g., "s4") or - if not applicable (i.e., if the d ata is compressed). An insamp value of zero (0) indicates th at the number of samples varies. Values less than zero in co lumns insamp and outsamp indicate that the total number of s amples must be evenly divisible by insamp. Strip indicates w hether to strip the authentication headers from the data; "y " means strip them and n means do not strip them.

WFDISC.description: The wfdisc table contains a waveform header file and descrip tive information. This table provides a pointer (or index) t o waveforms stored on disk. The waveforms themselves are sto red in ordinary disk files called wfdisc or '.w' files as a sequence of sample values (usually in binary representation) .

TIME.comment: Epoch time of first sample in file

FOFF.comment: Byte offset of data segment within file

WFFILE.description: The wffile table describes the files used in the Wave Form F iles managed by the Continuous Data Services Subsystem.

SAMPRATE.comment: Sampling Rate in samples per second

WFTAG.description: The wftag table links various identifiers (e.g., orid, arid, and stassid to wfid). Linkages can also be determined indir ectly using sta/chan/time; however, it is more efficient to use the wftag table.

XTAG.description: The xtag table links various identifiers (e.g., orid, arid, stassid, and wfid) to other identifiers. This table is a gen eralization of the wftag table, which is limited to linking exclusively to the wfdisc table. The thisdb column describes the database account for the record specified by thisid and thisname; thatdb describes the database account for the rec ord specified by thatid and thatname. When a parent/child ta ble exists between the records thisid should designate the p arent and thatid should designate the child.

THISNAME.comment: Key for thisid (grid, orid, ntid, and so on)

THATNAME.comment: Key for thatid (arid, orid, nfid, and so on)

THISDB.comment: Database account for the records specified by thisid and thisname

THATDB.comment: Database account for the records specified by thatid and thatname
